      "source_url": "https://thaqalayn.net/hadith/9/4/11/1",
      "text": [
        ": سألت أبا عبدالله عليه السلام عن تفسير بِسْمِ اللهِ الرَّحْمنِ الرَّحِيمِ قال: الباء بهاء الله والسين سناء الله والميم مجد الله"
      ],
      "translations": {
        "en.ammaar-muslim": [
          "1. [1/387] al-Kafi: A number of our companions from Ahmad b. Muhammad b. Khalid from al-Qasim b. Yahya from his grandfather al-Hasan b. Rashid from Abdallah b. Sinan who said: I asked Aba Abdillah عليه السلام about the interpretation of Bismillahi-r-Rahmani-r-Rahim. He said: The Ba is the Baha (Splendor) of Allah, the Sin is the Sana (Exaltedness) of Allah, and the Mim is the Majd (Magnificence) of Allah."
        ]
      }
    },
